<div class="content-post">
    <h4 class="title">Introduction of bams (bachelor of Ayurveda and Medicine and Surgery):</h4>
<p>Ayurveda is one of the oldest surviving medical systems in the world and is still widely practiced in India. A Bachelor of Ayurvedic Medicine and Surgery (BAMS) degree is a professional degree offered in the field of Ayurveda, one of the traditional forms of Indian medicine. This post will provide an overview of the BAMS admission process in India, discussing eligibility criteria, the application process and other important details.
</p>
</div>



<div class="content-post">
<h2 class="title">Eligibility Criteria for BAMS Admission 2023</h2>
Eligibility Criteria for BAMS Admission
<p>In order to get admission in a BAMS course, applicants must meet the eligibility criteria set by the concerned university and NTA. </p>

<ul class="list-item-point-thumb-right">
  <li>
The basic eligibility criteria for bams admission in India is that the applicant must have passed 10+2 (or equivalent) with Physics, Chemistry and Biology as compulsory subjects.
  </li>
  <li>
A minimum score of 50% in PCB (Physics, Chemistry and Biology) is required for bams admission
  </li>
  <li>
Must appear in NEET UG examination
  </li>
</ul>
</div>



<div class="content-post">
<h4 class="title">Application Process for BAMS Admission 2023</h4>
<ul class="list-item-point-thumb-right">

<li>Admission to bams course is generally based on the score obtained in NEET entrance exam. </li>
<li>Different states conduct bams counselling  independently or through a centralised bams counselling conduct by AICCC. </li>
<li>The bams application process usually starts in the month of June and ends by August/September.</li>
<li>Candidates must submit the required documents such as 10+2 mark sheet, date of birth proof (Aadhaar Card) and passport size photographs ,neet Admit Card ,neet score Card at the time of bams admission form submission. </li>


</div>


